{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
    "chapterNumber": 12,
    "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12",
    "summary": "Source text for 4 Maccabees 12 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:1",
      "text": "When he, too, had undergone blessed martyrdom, and died in the cauldron into which he had been thrown, the seventh, the youngest of all, came forward,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:2",
      "text": "whom the tyrant pitying, though he had been dreadfully reproached by his kindred,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:3",
      "text": "seeing him already encompassed with chains, had him brought nearer, and endeavored to counsel him, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:4",
      "text": "“You see the end of the madness of your kindred, for they have died in torture through disobedience. You, if disobedient, having been miserably tormented, will yourself perish prematurely.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:5",
      "text": "But if you obey, you will be my friend, and have a charge over the affairs of the kingdom.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:6",
      "text": "Having thus exhorted him, he sent for the boy’s mother, that, by showing compassion to her for the loss of so many sons, he might incline her, through the hope of safety, to make the survivor obedient.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:7",
      "text": "He, after his mother had urged him on in the Hebrew tongue, (as we will soon relate) said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:8",
      "text": "“Release me that I may speak to the king and all his friends.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:9",
      "text": "They, rejoicing exceedingly at the promise of the youth, quickly let him go.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:10",
      "text": "He, running up to the pans, said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:11",
      "text": "“Impious tyrant, and most blasphemous man, were you not ashamed, having received prosperity and a kingdom from God, to kill His servants, and to rack the doers of godliness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:12",
      "text": "Therefore the divine vengeance is reserving you for eternal fire and torments, which will cling to you for all time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:13",
      "text": "Weren’t you ashamed, man as you are, yet most savage, to cut out the tongues of men of like feeling and origin, and having thus abused to torture them?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:14",
      "text": "But they, bravely dying, fulfilled their religion toward God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:15",
      "text": "But you will groan as you deserve for having slain without cause the champions of virtue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:16",
      "text": "Therefore,” he continued, “I myself, being about to die,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:17",
      "text": "will not forsake my kindred.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:18",
      "text": "I call upon the God of my fathers to be merciful to my race.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:19",
      "text": "But you, both living and dead, he will punish.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.12.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:20",
      "text": "Thus having prayed, he hurled himself into the pans; and so expired.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
